_Section 9: IP Addressing_
_IP Addresses_

1 Internet Protocol (IP) Address          # пример из лекции это как почтовый адрес дома также и в сети 
layer 3 ip addresses are used by routers

2 layer 2 it is based on Mac addressing and switching 

3 ipv4 ipv6 

############################################################################################
_IPv4 Addressing_
1 4 separate numbers and divided by dots each divisions are called octets
id address   192.		168.			1.			4 

ip address  11000000  	10101000	000000001     00000100            

Subnet mask    255       255            255          0

Subnet mask  11111111    11111111     11111111       00000000    
		network bits   network bits   network bits   host bits  

2 Classes of IP Addresses 
each class has default subnet mask assigned by first octet classfull masks if using default subnet mask

Address       Value in first  Classful Mask         Classful Mask 
				Octet  		   Dotted decimal       (Prefix Notation)
Class A         1-126             255.0.0.0            /8
Class B         128-191           255.255.0.0          /16
Class C 		192-223           255.255.255.0        /24
Class D         224-239            n/a                  n/a

127 between class A class B

3 routable ips # publicy-routable ip addresses are globaly managed by ICANN. Public ip покупаются у вашего интернет провайдера.
ICAN всемирная организация которая продает эти ip (Ripe NCC европейская организация которая дает ip-address)

4 private ips # это приватные ip,которые недоступны во внешней сети

private ips!!!!
address class       Address range                   default subnet mask 
Class A        10.0.0.0 - 10.255.255.255.				255.0.0.0
Class B        172.16.0.0 - 172.31.255.255				255.255.0.0
Class C        192.168.0.0. - 192.168.255.255.          255.255.255.0

5 specialized ips
loopback addresses (127.x.x.x range)
Refer to the device itself and used for testing. These are most commonly used as 127.0.0.1 (localhost) device само устройство и используется только для тестирования как правило 

6 Automate Private Ip Addresses (APIPA)
Dynamically assigned by OS when DHCP server is unvaible and when address is not assigned manually.Range of 169.254.x.x.

APIPA save you when you have a problem with DHCP

description   Address Class     Address Range                  Default Subnet Mask
loopback      Class A 			127.0.0.1 - 127.255.255.255.      255.0.0.0
APIPA         Class B         169.254.0.0 - 169.254.255.255       255.255.0.0

ipconfig # windows 
ifconfig # linux       
Если там ты увидишь ip 169.254. значит проблема с DHCP 

7 Class A network address example:
ip address: 114.56.20.33.
Subnet Mask 255.0.0.0

Class B network address example:
ip address: 147.12.38.81.
Subnet Mask 255.255.0.0

Class C network address example:
ip address: 214.51.42.7.
Subnet Mask 255.255.255.0
